The Chief Whip of the Senate, Orji Uzor Kalu (APC,Abia), yesterday, resumed at the Senate after over six months of incarceration at the Kuje Correctional Centre. Sen. Kalu was jailed in December, 2019, over allegation of fraudulent misappropriation of Abia State’s treasury to the tune of N7.6bn during his days as governor between 1999 and 2007, to which he pleaded not guilty. Kalu, who spoke to journalists on arrival at the Senate, described his six-month incarceration as a “good experience”. The Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, who officially welcomed Kalu, congratulated him for resuming legislative duties. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here  UPDATE: Kalu returns to Senate after release from prison After 5 months in prison, Kalu set to resume at Senate on Tuesday Calls for by-election as Kalu spends 40 days in prison